# Implementation Plan

## Overview

This plan implements a two-phase bugfix for design token drift in the AO Figma Make kit. Phase 1 generates a comprehensive audit HTML page for Figma "Check Designs" validation. Phase 2 applies corrections to kit files after Figma identifies discrepancies. The exploratory testing approach writes bug condition and preservation tests BEFORE implementing the fix to understand and document the drift.

## Tasks

- [ ] 1. Write bug condition exploration test
  - **Property 1: Bug Condition** - Token Value Drift & Internal Inconsistency
  - **IMPORTANT**: Write this property-based test BEFORE implementing the fix
  - **CRITICAL**: This test MUST FAIL on unfixed code - failure confirms the bug exists
  - **DO NOT attempt to fix the test or the code when it fails**
  - **NOTE**: This test encodes the expected behavior - it will validate the fix when it passes after implementation
  - **GOAL**: Surface counterexamples that demonstrate token drift and internal inconsistencies exist
  - **Scoped PBT Approach**: Scope the property to concrete failing cases:
    - `action-primary-base`: tokens.md has `#008945`, tokens.json has `#00893e` — values must be identical across files
    - `action-secondary-base`: tokens.md has `#0a64c2`, tokens.json has `#0564c2` — values must be identical across files
  - Test: Parse `kit/tokens.md` (both markdown tables AND `:root` CSS block) and `kit/tokens.json` (`$value` fields)
  - For each token that appears in multiple files, assert the value is identical across all sources
  - For tokens where `isBugCondition(token)` holds: `token.value != figmaValue OR EXISTS(otherValue WHERE otherValue != token.value)`
  - Run test on UNFIXED code — expect FAILURE (this confirms the bug exists: conflicting values will be found)
  - Document counterexamples found (e.g., "`action-primary-base` is `#008945` in tokens.md but `#00893e` in tokens.json")
  - Mark task complete when test is written, run, and failure is documented
  - _Requirements: 1.3, 1.4_

- [ ] 2. Write preservation property tests (BEFORE implementing fix)
  - **Property 2: Preservation** - Correct Token & Structure Stability
  - **IMPORTANT**: Follow observation-first methodology
  - **IMPORTANT**: Write these tests BEFORE implementing the fix
  - Observe behaviour on UNFIXED code for non-buggy inputs (tokens that are consistent across files):
    - Observe: All `gray-*` tokens (10 through 100) have identical values in tokens.md tables, `:root` block, and tokens.json
    - Observe: Spacing scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, 40, 48, 56, 64px) is consistent across files
    - Observe: Shadow tokens (`--shadow`, `--shadow-md`, `--shadow-lg`, `--shadow-xl`) are consistent
    - Observe: Component HTML structure in `kit/components.md` uses `data-aods` attributes on all 14 component roots
    - Observe: Typography uses two-font system (SmileyFace for headings/CTAs, Inter for body/UI) in `kit/typography.md`
    - Observe: `kit/tokens.json` is valid JSON conforming to DTCG schema structure
  - Write property-based tests:
    - For all tokens where values are consistent across files (isBugCondition returns false), assert value equality across tokens.md, `:root` block, and tokens.json
    - For spacing scale, assert all 11 values match the 4px-base scale exactly
    - For component structure, assert all `data-aods` attributes are present and correct
    - For typography, assert SmileyFace/Inter font-family assignments are correct per type-scale class
  - Verify tests PASS on UNFIXED code (confirms baseline behaviour to preserve)
  - Mark task complete when tests are written, run, and passing on unfixed code
  - _Requirements: 3.1, 3.2, 3.3, 3.4, 3.5, 3.6_

- [ ] 3. Phase 1 - Generate design token audit page
  - [ ] 3.1 Create `examples/design-token-audit.html` with foundational structure
    - Single self-contained HTML file with all CSS inline in `<style>`
    - Include full `:root` token block from `kit/tokens.md`
    - Include full `@font-face` block from `kit/typography.md`
    - Include Inter Google Fonts `<link>` tag
    - White background with clear section dividers
    - Generous whitespace between sections for Figma overlay comparison
    - Page header section: title ("AO Design Token Audit"), version, generation date
    - _Requirements: 2.6_

  - [ ] 3.2 Add colour swatches section
    - Render every colour token as an 80×80px swatch with hex label below
    - Group by category with section headings:
      - Neutrals (gray-10 through gray-100)
      - Brand (brand-primary-base, brand-primary-light, brand-primary-dark)
      - Typography (type-primary, type-secondary, type-tertiary, shadow-overlay)
      - Action Primary (base, hover, focus, active, contrast, glow)
      - Action Secondary (base, hover, focus, active, contrast, glow)
      - Action Light (base, contrast, glow)
      - Action Dark (base, contrast, glow)
      - Action Inactive (base, contrast)
      - UI Surfaces (core, neutral, highlight, success, warning, error, light, dark — each with base/contrast/accent)
      - Food Palette (bread, toast, jam, simmer, heat, burn, steam, ice, water)
    - Each swatch uses `background-color: var(--token-name)` so Figma sees the actual rendered colour
    - _Requirements: 2.6_

  - [ ] 3.3 Add spacing blocks section
    - Render filled rectangles for each spacing token (spacing-1 through spacing-16)
