- [ ] 4. Phase 2 - Kit File Corrections (after Figma validation)
  - [ ] 4.1 Collect Figma Check Designs discrepancies from user
    - Open `examples/design-token-audit.html` in browser for Figma Check Designs comparison
    - Document all discrepancies identified by Figma (colours, radii, typography, component styling)
    - Categorise each discrepancy by affected file(s)
    - _Requirements: 1.1, 1.2, 1.3, 1.4, 1.5_

  - [ ] 4.2 Update `kit/tokens.md` with corrected values
    - Update markdown tables with Figma-verified hex values
    - Update the `:root` CSS block within the same file to match
    - Ensure internal consistency between tables and `:root` block
    - _Bug_Condition: isBugCondition(token) where token.value != figmaValue_
    - _Expected_Behavior: correctedValue == figmaValue for all affected tokens_
    - _Preservation: Tokens where isBugCondition returns false must retain original values_
    - _Requirements: 2.1, 2.2, 2.3, 2.4, 2.5_

  - [ ] 4.3 Update `kit/tokens.json` with corrected DTCG values
    - Update `$value` fields to match Figma-verified values
    - Maintain valid DTCG JSON schema structure
    - Ensure every corrected token matches the value now in `kit/tokens.md`
    - _Bug_Condition: isBugCondition(token) where token.value != figmaValue_
    - _Expected_Behavior: correctedValue == figmaValue for all affected tokens_
    - _Preservation: Non-buggy tokens retain original $value fields_
    - _Requirements: 2.1, 2.2, 2.3, 2.4, 2.5_

  - [ ] 4.4 Update `kit/components.md` if affected
    - If any inline CSS references or `:root` block in components.md uses corrected token values, update them
    - Preserve all HTML structure, class names, and `data-aods` attributes unchanged
    - _Bug_Condition: isBugCondition(token) where CSS in components.md references incorrect value_
    - _Expected_Behavior: All CSS custom property values match tokens.md_
    - _Preservation: Component HTML structure, class names, data-aods attributes unchanged_
    - _Requirements: 2.2, 2.3, 2.4, 3.4_

  - [ ] 4.5 Update `kit/typography.md` if affected
    - If font weights, sizes, or line-heights need correction per Figma, update the type scale table and CSS block
    - Preserve the two-font system (SmileyFace + Inter) unchanged
    - _Bug_Condition: isBugCondition(token) where typography specs differ from Figma_
    - _Expected_Behavior: All font specs match Figma library exactly_
    - _Preservation: Two-font system, font-family assignments unchanged_
    - _Requirements: 2.5, 3.5_

  - [ ] 4.6 Cross-validate consistency across all kit files
    - Verify every token appears with the same value in all files where it's referenced
    - Check tokens.md tables match `:root` block
    - Check tokens.md matches tokens.json `$value` fields
    - Check components.md CSS variable usage against defined tokens
    - Check typography.md CSS block against type scale table
    - _Requirements: 2.1, 2.2, 2.3, 2.4, 2.5, 3.1, 3.2, 3.3, 3.4, 3.5, 3.6_

  - [ ] 4.7 Verify bug condition exploration test now passes
    - **Property 1: Expected Behavior** - Token Value Consistency
    - **IMPORTANT**: Re-run the SAME test from task 1 - do NOT write a new test
    - The test from task 1 encodes the expected behavior (all tokens consistent across files)
    - When this test passes, it confirms the token drift bug is fixed
    - Run bug condition exploration test from step 1
    - **EXPECTED OUTCOME**: Test PASSES (confirms all token values are now consistent across kit files)
    - _Requirements: 2.1, 2.2, 2.3, 2.4, 2.5_

  - [ ] 4.8 Verify preservation tests still pass
    - **Property 2: Preservation** - Correct Token & Structure Stability
    - **IMPORTANT**: Re-run the SAME tests from task 2 - do NOT write new tests
    - Run preservation property tests from step 2
    - **EXPECTED OUTCOME**: Tests PASS (confirms no regressions to spacing, shadows, component structure, typography system)
    - Confirm all tests still pass after fix (no regressions)
    - _Requirements: 3.1, 3.2, 3.3, 3.4, 3.5, 3.6_

- [ ] 5. Checkpoint - Ensure all tests pass
  - Ensure all property tests pass (both bug condition and preservation)
  - Verify the audit page still renders correctly with corrected token values
  - Confirm existing example HTML pages (`examples/componentLibrary.html`, etc.) still render correctly
  - Ask the user if questions arise

