## Notes

- Phase 1 (audit page generation) can proceed immediately — it creates a new file without modifying existing ones
- Phase 2 is user-driven: it requires the user to provide Figma Check Designs discrepancy results before corrections can be applied
- The bug condition test (task 1) validates internal consistency between kit files — it will FAIL initially due to known conflicts (action-primary-base, action-secondary-base)
- The preservation test (task 2) validates tokens that are already consistent — it should PASS on unfixed code
- Tasks 1 and 2 are independent of Phase 1 and can be written in parallel with audit page generation
- The audit page is large but must remain a single self-contained HTML file per project conventions
